https://mrdata.usgs.gov/metadata/mrds.txt
Citation:
      Citation_Information:
        Originator: U.S. Geological Survey
        Publication_Date: 2005
        Title: Mineral Resources Data System
        Edition: 20160315
        Geospatial_Data_Presentation_Form: map
        Publication_Information:
          Publication_Place: Reston, Virginia
          Publisher: U.S. Geological Survey
        Online_Linkage: https://mrdata.usgs.gov/mrds/

Development status meanings:
https://mrdata.usgs.gov/mrds/compact/dd.php?group=Site+characteristics
Selected records with dev_stat (development status) == Producer, Plant, or Past Producer


## Sriram et al layers:
Sriram, Sumithra & Huettmann, Falk. (2017). A Global Model of Predicted Peregrine Falcon ( Falco peregrinus ) Distribution with Open Source GIS Code and 104 Open Access Layers for use by the global public. Earth System Science Data Discussions. 1-39. 10.5194/essd-2016-65.

doi:10.5194/essd-2016-65, 2017

## Zabel crop suitability
Article Source: Global Agricultural Land Resources – A High Resolution Suitability Evaluation and Its Perspectives until 2100 under Climate Change Conditions
Zabel F, Putzenlechner B, Mauser W (2014) Global Agricultural Land Resources – A High Resolution Suitability Evaluation and Its Perspectives until 2100 under Climate Change Conditions. PLOS ONE 9(9): e107522. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0107522
http://geoportal-glues.ufz.de/stories/globalsuitability.html
http://data1-glues.ufz.de//download/glues_crop_suitability/overall_cropsuit_i/
1981-2010.

